1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the construction of interference-free zero correlation zone (IF-ZCZ) sequence sets, which is a topic related to information theory. 
2. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper discusses the implementation of banks of matched filters, which is a signal processing technique. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new construction method for IF-ZCZ sequence sets, which involves designing a finite Zak transform lattice tessellation. This involves the use of algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the computational complexity of the implementation of banks of matched filters, which is a topic related to numerical analysis. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper proposes a method for constructing IF-ZCZ sequence sets that have sparse and highly structured Zak and Fourier spectra, which can decrease the computational complexity of the implementation of the banks of matched filters.
